    ],
    "comments": "The Simple Span measure primarily taps into active maintenance of information in working memory, as participants need to hold and recall a sequence of stimuli. It also reflects the limited capacity of working memory, as the span is determined by the maximum number of items that can be remembered. Additionally, it involves updating and representation of information as new items are added to the sequence."
}

