        "Attention"
    ],
    "comments": "The Stroop incongruent-congruent contrast primarily measures inhibition/suppression as participants must suppress the automatic word reading response. It also taps into interference control, as subjects need to control the interference from the conflicting word meaning. Attention is involved as participants must selectively attend to the ink color while ignoring the word meaning. This measure captures the additional cognitive control required to overcome the conflict in incongruent trials compared to congruent trials."
}

